# Copy to `.dev.vars` for local `wrangler dev`. NEVER commit `.dev.vars`.
# These are LOCAL-ONLY dev vars. Production secrets live in Worker secrets
# (`wrangler secret put`), never in wrangler.toml [vars] and never in git.

# ─── Client-id HMAC salt ([SECURITY/Opus] "Client identification" + "Secrets") ─
# Keyed salt for the non-reversible per-visitor session hash used by the neuron
# budget's per-visitor cap. In PRODUCTION this is a Worker SECRET
# (`wrangler secret put HASH_SALT`), NEVER wrangler.toml [vars] and NEVER git.
# Locally, set any >=16-char random value. Missing salt fails closed.
HASH_SALT="local-dev-salt-change-me-0123456789"

# ─── Admin credential ([SECURITY/Opus] admin/ingest isolation, Phase 1) ────────
# argon2id hash of the admin password (server-side session auth for the ingest /
# eval-management surface). A Worker SECRET in production. Unset here by default;
# the admin surface is unreachable until this lands in Phase 1.
# ADMIN_CREDENTIAL_HASH=""
